        <title>Reflections</title>
        <author>
            <name>Judy He and Jessica Xia</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://ourcovidstories.github.io/dusk-till-dawn/reflections.html"/>
        <id>https://ourcovidstories.github.io/dusk-till-dawn/reflections.html</id>

        <updated>2021-12-06T14:14:59-08:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                    At the present moment, looking back at what has happened in the past year, we see how the world has changed from various&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At the present moment, looking back at what has happened in the past year, we see how the world has changed from various aspects. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">As two college students who made different decisions upon the outbreak of the pandemic, we both faced challenges in our lives.¬†</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Attending Zoom University, Judy had to cope with the time-zone difference, while Jessica also had to adjust to the online platform, attending lectures without being physically on campus. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">During the pandemic, our real-life interactions with people were limited; hence, we treasured the opportunity of meeting and spending time with our friends. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">At times when we were feeling pressured and full of negativity, our families and friends were the ones who brought a ray of sunshine in the darkness.¬†</span></p>
<p>As we returned to campus this fall quarter, everything felt so new yet so familiar. Coming through the pandemic, we have never cherished the time in campus more. We are grateful for the past journey, and are more than ready to welcome the new challenges.</p>
<p>From Dusk till Dawn, and towards brighter days. üíó</p>
<p>¬†</p>
<p>Judy and Jessica</p>
<p>December 2021 in Los Angeles</p>
